==Anglo-Saxon==

===Etymology===
*Xerxis is from the Greek Ξερξες.

===Pronunciation===
*Kser·ksis

===Proper noun===
'''xerxis'''  {{m}}

# [[Xerxes]], the King of Persia from 485 BC to 465 BC

====Declension====
*''Singular:'' se Xerxis, þæs Xerxises, þǽm Xerxise, þone Xerxis
*''Plural:'' þá Xerxisas, þǽra Xerxisa, þǽm Xerxisum, þá Xerxisas

